race.comment: Very moderate race with a couple of the better chances off forgive runs. STARTLING STAR (2) is the least experienced and has the least convictions. Maiden winner two back then fourth and beaten a couple of lengths in heavy ground last time. One of the few with upside and can find winning form again. OPAL TANGO (7) was sent out a heavily bet favourite last time but finished at the tail after pulling up lame. Previous form good for this and gets chance to bounce back straight away in a weak middle distance race. DANDY'S GEM (5) is going pretty well with placings at last two. On speed runner drawn to give a sight. ALMAYA (4) turned in a poor run last time dropping out to the tail. Much better than that and would go close on the figure the start prior. WESTCOAST EXPRESS (11) is long overdue but has been winding up late last couple and does come into this with the light weight after the claim.
